<tt>eix</tt> is a set of utilities for searching and diffing the local Portage tree and overlays using a binary cache.

It is made to be more efficient and flexible than the <tt>emerge --search</tt> command. <tt>eix</tt> comes with colorized output which helps users easily find the needed package information.

== Installation ==

Install {{Package|app-portage/eix}}:

{{Emerge|app-portage/eix}}

== Configuration ==

=== Updating the cache ===

After the installation has finished, it is important to update the cache to index all packages on the system. Running following command will update the local <tt>eix</tt> cache:

{{RootCmd|eix-update}}

If [[Overlay|overlays]] are used, it is recommended to configure <tt>eix</tt> to synchronize them too:

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/eix-sync.conf|1=
*
}}

To spare some typing work, run following command:

{{RootCmd|eix-sync}}

The above command is a shorthand way to running these commands sequentially:

{{RootCmd
|emerge --sync
|eix-update
|eix-diff}}

Check <tt>eix-sync</tt> with the <code>--dry-run</code> option for more information:

{{RootCmd|eix-sync -nv}}

=== Using tmpfs cache ===

This breaks <tt>eix</tt> because {{Path|/var/cache/eix}} is missing when {{Path|/var/cache}} is mounted:

{{RootCmd|grep /var/cache /etc/fstab|output=<pre>
none /var/cache tmpfs size=512m 0 0
</pre>}}

The simple solution is to move the <tt>eix</tt> cache file away from the default location:

{{RootCmd|echo EIX_CACHEFILE{{=}}%{EPREFIX}/var/cache/eix-portage.eix >> /etc/eixrc/00-eixrc
|eix --dump {{!}} grep EIX_CACHEFILE|output=<pre>
EIX_CACHEFILE=%{EPREFIX}/var/cache/eix-portage.eix
# EIX_CACHEFILE=%{EPREFIX}/var/cache/eix/portage.eix</pre>}}

One side effect is needing to run <tt>eix-update</tt> after reboot which will take a few seconds.

=== Adding overlays to the cache ===

To search not only in the portage tree but all the overlays, add overlays to the cache:

{{RootCmd
|eix-remote update
|eix-sync
}}

